	CancelCall(context.Context, *CancelCallRequest) (*CancelCallResponse, error)
	// SetRemote tells the per-call runner where to send RTP. For inbound
	// calls comedia learning works fine (we send back to whoever sent us
	// the first packet). For outbound calls we know the destination
	// upfront from the SDP answer; SetRemote unblocks the active sender
	// so the greeting starts flowing immediately on ACK rather than
	// waiting for the callee's first frame.
