	// TapCall streams every RTP packet flowing through the specified
	// call (both directions) for as long as the caller stays
	// connected. Zero-copy-adjacent: the edge duplicates the packet
	// bytes into the stream without parsing RTP, so even malformed /
	// non-RTP payloads show up verbatim for post-hoc Wireshark
	// analysis. Unknown call id → NotFound. Bounded per-call queue;
	// a slow consumer drops frames rather than back-pressuring the
	// production audio path.
